{"id":1468,"title":"Pharmacology for the geriatric surgical patient.","abstract":"Alterations in pharmacokinetics and pharmacodynamics place geriatric patients at an increased risk of experiencing an adverse drug event. The incidence of medication-related adverse events can be decreased with careful selection of agents and appropriate dosage adjustments. ","date":"2014-12-03","categories":"Chemically-Induced Disorders","split":"test","url":"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/25459548","annotations":[{"name":"Pharmacology","weight":0.834159,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmacology"},{"name":"Pharmacodynamics","weight":0.810695,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmacodynamics"},{"name":"Pharmacokinetics","weight":0.810695,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Pharmacokinetics"},{"name":"Adverse drug reaction","weight":0.796984,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adverse_drug_reaction"},{"name":"Surgery","weight":0.711024,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Surgery"},{"name":"Adverse effect","weight":0.704378,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Adverse_effect"},{"name":"Patient","weight":0.681913,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Patient"},{"name":"Drug","weight":0.678276,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Drug"},{"name":"Risk","weight":0.170177,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Risk"},{"name":"Incidence (epidemiology)","weight":0.167001,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Incidence_(epidemiology)"},{"name":"Geriatrics","weight":0.147891,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Geriatrics"},{"name":"Dose (biochemistry)","weight":0.0650786,"wikipedia_article":"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dose_(biochemistry)"}]}
